         <div type="commentary" subtype="linebyline">
            <list>
               <item corresp="#lb1" xml:space="preserve">
            <ref>1</ref>
            <p>
              ὀστᾶ "cores" is the tentative interpretation by Préaux (cf. e.g. Gal.
              <emph rend="italics">Simpl.</emph>
              XII 342.1-3 ὀστᾶ κεκαυμένα διαφορητικῆς καὶ ξηραντικῆς ἱκανῶς ἐστι δυνάμεως, μάλιστα δέ φασιν ἔνιοι τὰ τῶν ἀνθρώπων δύνασθαι τοῦτο) but the characters can also belong to a longer word, like e.g. the ingredient να]ρ̣δ̣οστά[χυος "spikenard", which appears in the composition of several different types of eye-salves.
            </p>
          </item>
            </list>
